Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/eurasian-heritage-centre.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/historical/hajjah-fatimah-mosque.html

Description2: With its tilting European-style minaret and Chinese tiling, the Hajjah Fatimah Mosque is one of the most unique mosques in Singapore.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/haw-par-villa.html

Description2: A visit to the Haw Par Villa theme park is an unforgettable journey into Chinese folklore and mythology.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/nus-baba-house.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/historical/hong-san-see.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/historical/capitol-building-singapore.html

Description2: Now undergoing massive restoration works, Capitol Building will emerge as Singapore’s premier entertainment hub next year.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/esplanade-theatres-on-the-bay.html
Image Text: Catch a world-class opera or pop concert at Singapore’s premier performing arts centre.
DESCRIPTION: This boldly designed performing arts centre has become a memorable part of Singapore’s skyline.
Description2: The Esplanade is boldly designed performing arts centre that has become a memorable part of Singapore’s skyline.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/gardens-by-the-bay.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/the-interlace.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/parkroyal-on-pickering.html

Description2: PARKROYAL on Pickering is a luxurious garden oasis in downtown Singapore.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/historical/lau-pa-sat.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/malay-heritage-centre.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/peranakan-museum.html

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/fun-with-animals/river-safari-singapore.html
Image Text: Meet manatees, monkeys and more as you ride the world's rivers at River Safari, Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: At the River Safari Singapore, meet manatees and monkeys, piranhas and pandas, as they congregate in and around the park’s waters.
Description2: The River Safari Singapore is a fascinating new wildlife park that recreates life in and around the world’s rivers.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/mount-faber.html
Image Text: Spend a unique evening overlooking spectacular views on a cable car in Singapore's Mount Faber.
DESCRIPTION: Getting to this hilltop dining and entertainment spot at Mount Faber by cable car  is half the fun.
Description2: Getting to the hilltop dining and entertainment spot at Mount Faber by cable car is half the fun.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/fun-with-animals/night-safari.html
Image Text: Enter a world of nocturnal creatures at the Night Safari, Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: Instead of going to a club, pop into another popular nightspot, the Night Safari, and mingle with a different crowd of animals at this special zoo.
Description2: Head to the Night Safari for an after dark visit to the weird and wonderful creatures of the night.
Opening Hours: Daily, 7.30pm - 12am .Last ticket sale at 11.15pm.F and B and retail outlets open from 5.30pm

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/singapore-islands/pulau-ubin.html
DESCRIPTION: Gravel roads, lush forests and abundant wildlife – Pulau Ubin is a living showcase of what Singapore was like in the 1960s.
Description2: Hop on a bumboat to the island of Pulau Ubin if you want a taste of nature and rustic village life, away from the hustle and bustle of Singapore.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/little-india.html
Image Text: Immerse yourself in the rich culture of Little India, Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: Little India is a buzzing historic area that shows off the best of Singapore’s Indian community from vibrant culture to incredible shopping.
Description2: Little India is a buzzing historic district that shows off the best of Singapore’s Indian community, from vibrant culture to ethnic-inspired shopping.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/orchard.html
Image Text: Orchard Road, Singapore is nothing short of a shopper's paradise.
NAME2: Orchard Road, Singapore: Asia's Most Famous Shopping Street
DESCRIPTION: Orchard Road, Asia’s most famous shopping street, is home to fashion favourites, specialist stores and loads of other lifestyle choices.
Description2: Don’t miss a trip to Orchard Road. Asia’s most famous shopping street is home to fashion favourites, specialist stores and loads of other lifestyle choices.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/reserves/macritchie-nature-reserve.html
Image Text: MacRitchie Reservoir is nature’s playground for those who love the great outdoors.
DESCRIPTION: The attractions around MacRitchie Reservoir is a playground of nature for those who love the outdoors.
Description2: The attractions around MacRitchie Reservoir caters to fitness fanatics, water sports enthusiasts and nature lovers.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/gardens-by-the-bay.html
Image Text: Be mesmerised by stunning waterfront views at the award-winning horticultural destination that is Gardens by the Bay.
DESCRIPTION: This sprawling garden in the city provides mesmerising waterfront views across three gardens, spanning over 101 hectares of reclaimed land.
Description2: Gardens by the Bay provides mesmerising waterfront views across three gardens, spanning over 101 hectares of reclaimed land.
Opening Hours: Bay South Outdoor Gardens Daily, 5am - 2am Cooled Conservatories and OCBC Skyway Daily, 9am - 9pm(last ticket sale at 8pm).Far East Organization Children's Garden Tuesday* to Friday, 10am - 7pm(last admission: 6.30pm)*Closed on Tuesday if a public holiday falls on the preceding Monday Weekends and public holidays, 9am - 9pm(last admission: 8.30pm)

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/civic-district.html
Image Text: Immerse yourself in a day of history and culture at the Civic District, Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: The Civic District is where Singapore’s historical, architectural and cultural heritage started.
Description2: The Civic District is where Singapore’s historical, architectural and cultural heritage starts.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/harbourfront.html
Image Text: HarbourFront, Singapore is your exciting gateway to entertainment and Singapore's outlying islands.
DESCRIPTION: HarbourFront is the place to go if you're hopping on a cruise from Singapore, taking a regional ferry or simply want to eat, shop or relax.
Description2: HarbourFront is the place to go if you're hopping on a cruise from Singapore, taking a ferry to the outlying islands or simply want to eat, shop or relax.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/bras-basah-bugis.html
Image Text: There’s nowhere else quite like shopping at Bugis.
DESCRIPTION: The Bras Basah.Bugis Precinct is the arts and heritage district in Singapore's civic centre, and home to museums and monuments.
Description2: The Bras Basah.Bugis Precinct is the vibrant arts and cultural district in the heart of Singapore's civic centre, and home to top museums and monuments.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/arts/museums-galleries/8q-sam.html
Image Text: SAM at 8Q is the funkier sister of the Singapore Art Museum.
DESCRIPTION: An extension of the Singapore Art Museum, SAM at 8Q features contemporary art exhibitions and is home to a Moving Image Gallery, where film screenings are held.
Description2: SAM at 8Q at the Singapore Art Museum showcases the works of Singapore contemporary artists.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/places-of-worship/jamae-mosque.html
Image Text: The Jamae Mosque in Singapore is one of the oldest mosques in Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: Also known as Masjid Chulia, Jamae Mosque is one of Singapore’s oldest mosques and a prominent landmark in Chinatown since the 1820s.
Description2: Jamae Mosque (or Masjid Chulia) is one of Singapore’s oldest mosques and a prominent landmark in Chinatown since the 1820s.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/arts/performance-arts/institute-of-contemporary-arts.html
Image Text: Be inspired by the architecture and creativity at the Institute of Contemporary Arts, Singapore.
ADDRESSSTREETNAME: LASALLE College of the Arts, 1 McNally Street
DESCRIPTION: This experimental art space housed in a tertiary arts college will help you deepen your understanding of contemporary art.
Description2: Housed in a tertiary arts college, the Institute of Contemporary Arts Singapore will help you deepen your appreciation for experimental artworks.
Opening Hours: Tuesday to Sunday, 12pm - 7pm, Closed on Monday and public holidays

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/viewpoints/singapore-flyer.html
Image Text: Marvel at spectacular panoramas of the city skyline from the Singapore Flyer.
DESCRIPTION: This giant observation wheel offers 360-degree city views, a panorama that stretches to parts of Malaysia and Indonesia on a clear day.
Description2: The Singapore Flyer not only offers you stunning views of the city, but is one of the city’s most recognisable architectural icons.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/marina-bay-sands.html
Image Text: The breathtaking Marina Bay Sands is a sheer modern architectural triumph.
DESCRIPTION: A feat of engineering, an architectural statement and a sheer aesthetic triumph, Marina Bay Sands<sup>®</sup> has upped the ante for buildings in Singapore.
Description2: Superlatives naturally spring to mind when beholding Marina Bay Sands®. Its bold, swooping curves, steep slopes, and soaring spaces defy gravity and evoke awe.
Opening Hours: SkyPark<sup® Operating Hours - Monday to Thursday, 9:30am – 10pm, Friday to Sunday, 9:30am – 11pm, Shoppes Daily, 10am – 10pm (hours vary by store)

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/marina-barrage.html
Image Text: More than just an ordinary dam, the Marina Barrage is an ideal recreational space.
DESCRIPTION: This innovative facility not only supplies water to Singaporeans and helps alleviate floods but also doubles up as a place for family fun.
Description2: The Marina Barrage not only supplies water to Singaporeans and helps alleviate floods but also doubles up as a place for family fun.
Opening Hours: Marina Barrage - All day  Information Counter Daily, 9am – 9pm

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/henderson-waves.html
Image Text: Explore some of the city’s best parks and trails, such as the Southern Ridges Walk.
DESCRIPTION: Lush jungle is broken up with a seriously creative twist in the fantastic form of the Henderson Waves bridge.
Description2: With the Henderson Waves bridge, form meets function to stunning effect.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/reserves/labrador-nature-reserve.html
Image Text: Labrador Nature Reserve in Singapore is a beautiful park that is rich with biodiversity.
DESCRIPTION: With its rich biodiversity and war relics, nature lovers and history enthusiasts will find plenty to do at Labrador Nature Reserve.
Description2: With its rich biodiversity and war relics, nature lovers and history enthusiasts will find plenty to do at Labrador Nature Reserve.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/marina-bay-area.html
Image Text: Marina Bay Sands® is an integrated resort with experiences like no other.
NAME2: Marina Bay Singapore: Attractions & Things to do
DESCRIPTION: Marina Bay represents all things modern and super-stylish, from trendy dining destinations to exciting leisure spots.
Description2: Marina Bay represents all things modern and super-stylish in Singapore, from trendy dining destinations to fun leisure spots.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/resorts/marina-bay-sands.html
DESCRIPTION: This iconic integrated resort boasts luxury accommodations, upscale shopping and an infinity pool with unparalleled views of the city.
Description2: Marina Bay Sands® boasts luxury accommodations, upscale shopping and an infinity pool with unparalleled views of the city.
Opening Hours: Opening hours varies. Please visit the official website for more information.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/reserves/chek-jawa.html
Image Text: Bird lovers can spot rare species from a 21-metre tall viewing tower at Chek Jawa.
DESCRIPTION: A world away from shopping malls and glitzy hotels, this natural wonder is one of Singapore’s richest eco-systems.
Description2: A world away from shopping malls and glitzy hotels, the natural wonder of Chek Jawa is one of Singapore’s richest eco-systems.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/viewpoints/merlion-park.html
Image Text: Come and see the Singapore icon that is half-fish and half-lion at the Merlion Park.
NAME2: Merlion Park, Singapore: Attractions & Things to Do
DESCRIPTION: Half-fish and half-lion, the iconic Merlion resides at the waterfront Merlion Park.
Description2: Merlion Park houses a Singapore icon that is half-fish and half-lion, and famous throughout the world.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/viewpoints/marina-bay-sands-skypark.html
Image Text: Take in stunning views from an infinity pool and observation deck in the clouds at the Marina Bay Sands SkyPark.
DESCRIPTION: The Marina Bay Sands<sup>®</sup> SkyPark is a roof like no other, perched 200 metres in the air with an infinity pool and observation deck in the clouds.
Description2: The Marina Bay Sands<sup>®</sup> SkyPark is a roof like no other, perched 200 metres in the air with an infinity pool and observation deck in the clouds.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/resorts/resorts-world-sentosa.html
Image Text: From world-class theme parks to celebrity restaurants, Resorts World Sentosa has it all.
DESCRIPTION: Experience endless excitement at Resorts World Sentosa with a variety of attractions and entertainment hot spots.
Description2: Whether it’s themes parks, world-class performances or celebrity restaurants, you’ll never run out of things to do at Resorts World™ Sentosa.
Opening Hours: Opening hours differ for the various attractions.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/the-southern-ridges.html
Image Text: From world-class theme parks to celebrity restaurants, Resorts World Sentosa has it all.
ADDRESSSTREETNAME: Henderson Road, Mount Faber Park, Telok Blangah Hill Park
DESCRIPTION: This 10-km stretch of connecting trails lets you walk among the trees to observe a wide variety of flora and fauna in their natural habitat.
Description2: The Southern Ridges is a 10-km stretch of connecting trails which lets you walk among the trees to observe a wide variety of flora and fauna in their natural habitat.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/reserves/sungei-buloh-wetland-reserve.html
Image Text: Get up close with a wide variety of flora and fauna in their natural habitat at this Singapore Garden.
DESCRIPTION: This ecological wonder will transport you into a world rich in animal and plant life.
Description2: The ecological wonder of Sungei Buloh will transport you into a world rich in animal and plant life.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/fun-with-animals/sea-aquarium.html
Image Text: Explore a world rich with animal and plant life at the Sungei Buloh Wetland Reserve.
DESCRIPTION: Immerse yourself underwater at the S.E.A. Aquarium™ and discover more than 100,000 marine animals.
Description2: Immerse yourself underwater at the S.E.A. Aquarium™ and take a look into the planet’s largest window to the ocean.
Opening Hours: Open daily at 10am.Closing time varies. Please visit the official website for more information.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/singapore-river.html
Image Text: Take a stroll along the Singapore River and see how the city came to be.
DESCRIPTION: Get to know historic Singapore River and its famous quays: Boat Quay, Clarke Quay and Robertson Quay. After all, this is where it all began.
Description2: Get to know the historic Singapore River and its famous quays: Boat Quay, Clarke Quay and Robertson Quay. This, after all, is where it all began.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/joochiat-katong.html
Image Text: Spend a day exploring heritage shophouses and quaint stores at Joo Chiat/Katong.
DESCRIPTION: Discover Peranakan culture as you stroll past heritage shophouses, quaint stores and eateries in this charming corner of eastern Singapore.
Description2: Discover Peranakan culture as you stroll past heritage shophouses, quaint stores and eateries in Joo Chiat/Katong, a charming corner of eastern Singapore.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/sentosa.html
Image Text: Get ready for laughs, thrills and loads of fun in the sun at Sentosa Island.
DESCRIPTION: Sentosa Island is Singapore’s favourite leisure destination with exciting attractions, golden beaches, luxe retreats and the country’s first integrated resort.
Description2: Sentosa Island is Singapore’s favourite leisure destination, with more than 500 hectares filled with exciting attractions, golden beaches, luxe retreats and the country’s first integrated resort, Resorts World Sentosa.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/places-to-see/chinatown.html
Image Text: Chinatown, Singapore is a bustling mix of old-world charm and modern delights.
DESCRIPTION: Singapore’s historic Chinatown is a bustling mix of old and new, filled with traditional shops and markets as well as cool stores and cafes.
Description2: Singapore’s legendary Chinatown is a bustling mix of old and new, filled with traditional shops and night markets as well as cool stores and cafes.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/places-of-worship/buddha-tooth-relic-temple-museum.html
NAME2: Buddha Tooth Relic Temple & Museum in Singapore
DESCRIPTION: This Tang-styled Chinese Buddhist temple in Chinatown gets its name from what the Buddhists regard as the Sacred Buddha Tooth Relic.
Description2: The Buddha Tooth Relic Temple & Museum is a Tang-styled Chinese Buddhist temple in Chinatown that gets its name from the Sacred Buddha Tooth Relic.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/arts/museums-galleries/national-gallery-singapore.html
DESCRIPTION: Take in the region’s newest and largest museum of modern Singapore and Southeast Asian art housed within two of Singapore’s awe-inspiring national monuments.
Description2: Take in the region’s newest and largest museum of modern Singapore and Southeast Asian art housed within two of Singapore’s awe-inspiring national monuments.
Opening Hours: Effective from 24 November 2015, Sunday to Thursday and  public holidays,10am - 7pm ,Friday to Saturday and  eve of public holidays, 10am - 10pm

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/fun-things-to-do/universal-studios-singapore.html
Image Text: Southeast Asia's first Hollywood movie theme park offers a dizzying selection of entertainment offerings.
DESCRIPTION: Step into the glamorous world of movies at this world-class theme park located within Resorts World Sentosa™.
Description2: Universal Studios Singapore™ at Resorts World™ Sentosa is a movie-themed entertainment park that the whole family can enjoy.
Opening Hours: Open daily at 10am.Closing time varies. Please visit the official website for more information.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/fun-things-to-do/science-centre.html
Image Text: Adults and kids of all ages who are not even science buffs will have fun at the Singapore Science Centre.
DESCRIPTION: This enlightening attraction holds the largest collection of educational materials devoted to science in Singapore.
Description2: Singapore Science Centre holds the largest collection of educational materials devoted to science in the country.
Opening Hours: Science Centre Singapore Daily, 10am – 6pm(last admission: 5.15pm) .Omni Theatre Daily, 12pm – 6pm (last show: 6pm) . Snow City Daily, 10am – 6pm (last admission: 5pm) School and public holidays, 10am – 7pm (last admission: 6pm)

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/fuk-tak-chi-museum.html
Image Text: Marvel at the Fuk Tak Chi Museum's carefully restored architecture in the heart of Chinatown.
NAME2: Fuk Tak Chi Museum & Places of Interest
DESCRIPTION: Fuk Tak Chi Museum was once the oldest Chinese temple in Singapore and is an elegant example of restored architecture in Chinatown.
Description2: Fuk Tak Chi Museum was once the oldest Chinese temple in Singapore and is an elegant example of restored architecture in Chinatown.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/culture-heritage/heritage-discovery/katong-antique-house.html
Image Text: Marvel at antiques and heirlooms worthy of any museum collection at the Katong Antique House.
NAME2: Katong Antique House Singapore: Peranakan Heritage
DESCRIPTION: Step into this fully restored bona fide Peranakan family home, and admire the many antiques and heirlooms worthy of any museum collection.
Description2: Step into this fully restored bona fide Peranakan family home, and admire the many antiques and heirlooms worthy of any museum collection.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/chinese-garden.html
Image Text: Step back in time to ancient China at the beautiful Chinese Garden, Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: A tranquil patch of imperial China in the west of Singapore is pleasant respite from the bustle of the city.
Description2: A tranquil patch of imperial China in the west of Singapore is pleasant respite from the bustle of the city.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/east-coast-park.html
Image Text: Whether you prefer water sports, rollerblading or cycling, find a myriad of things to do at East Coast Park, Singapore.
ADDRESSSTREETNAME: Along East Coast Parkway and East Coast Park Service Road
DESCRIPTION: With so many attractions packed into this 15-km stretch of beaches, you’ll never run out of things to do.
Description2: With so many attractions packed into the 15-km stretch of beaches at East Coast Park, you’ll never run out of things to do.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/fort-canning-park.html
Image Text: Take a stroll back in time at Fort Canning Park, Singapore - a landmark full of history.
ADDRESSSTREETNAME: Bounded by Hill Street, Canning Rise, Clemenceau Avenue and River Valley Road
DESCRIPTION: Whether you’re a history buff, music fan or nature lover, this historic landmark on a hill is full of surprises.
Description2: Whether you’re a history buff, music fan or nature lover, this historic Fort Canning Park has something for everyone.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/singapore-islands/kusu-island.html
DESCRIPTION: If you’re looking for local heritage off the beaten track with a good dash of nature, Kusu Island hits the spot.
Description2: Kusu Island lies to the south of Singapore, and has a wonderful mix of local heritage and beach activities.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/fun-with-animals/jurong-bird-park.html
Image Text: Enjoy close encounters with some of our prettiest and rarest feathered friends at the Jurong Bird Park.
NAME2: Jurong Bird Park, Singapore: Attractions & Things to Do
DESCRIPTION: Jurong Bird Park has almost every species to impress avian lovers, along with fun exhibits, interactive shows, and of course, its charming residents.
Description2: Jurong Bird Park has almost every species to impress avian lovers, along with fun exhibits, interactive shows, and of course, its charming residents.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/nature-wildlife/parks-gardens/hortpark.html
Image Text: Escape the buzz of the city at HortPark, Singapore.
DESCRIPTION: Lose yourself in this dreamscape of stunning gardens that will make you forget the bustle of city.
Description2: HortPark is a gorgeous collection of stunning gardens and plants that will make you  forget about the bustle of city.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/recreation-leisure/fun-things-to-do/adventure-cove.html
Image Text: Adventure Cove Waterpark™, Singapore is the perfect place to have fun with loved ones.
DESCRIPTION: Make a big splash at this aquatic adventure park at Resorts World™ Sentosa.
Description2: Adventure Cove Waterpark™ Singapore at Resorts World™ Sentosa promises a day of wet and wild fun in the sun.

Name: www.yoursingapore.com/en/see-do-singapore/architecture/modern/lassalle-college-of-the-arts.html
Image Text: Lasalle College of the Arts pushes the boundaries of creativity in architecture.
DESCRIPTION: How can something that fits so perfectly into a cityscape evoke nature as well? It all lies in the design of Lasalle College of the Arts.
Description2: How can something that fits so perfectly into a cityscape evoke nature as well? It all lies in the design of Lasalle College of the Arts.
Opening Hours: Administration Office Monday to Friday, 9am – 6pm.Visitors can still walk around the campus after office opening hours.
